title: Measurement of the 239Pu(n,f) prompt fission neutron spectrum from 10 keV to 10 MeV induced by neutrons of energy 1 - 20 MeV

spectrum from 10 keV to 10 MeV induced by neutrons of
energy 1 - 20 MeV

x4freetext: The experiment was carried out at the
WNR facility,part of the Los Alamos Neutron Science
Center at Los Alamos National Laboratory.
239Pu was placed inside
fission parallel- plate avalanche counter consisting
of 10 individual PPAC volumes. Each volume was
separated from neighboring volumes by a 5 mu-m
platinum plate and consists of a titanium foil with 5
mg deposit of pure 239Pu. Each deposit is 4 cm in
diameter, yielding a target density of approximately
400 mu-g/cm2 for each volume.
Fission fragments were were detected in a
multilayer fission chamber consisting of 10 individual
parallel-plate avalanche counter volumes. Each volume
is separated from neighboring volumes by a 5 mu-m
platinum plate and consists of a titanium foil with
5 mu-g of pure 239Pu electro-deposited on either side.
Each deposit is 4 cm in diameter, yielding a target
density of approximately 400 mu-g/cm2 for each volume.
Fission fragments from neutron induced fission of 239Pu
are detected via an electron avalanche initiated by
ionization of 4.2-torr isobutane gas.
Primary as well as secondary neutron energy was
determined by time of flight. Proton beam consists of
macropulses with repetition rate of 100 Hz. Each
macropulse was composed of series of 347 micropulses
150 ps wide and separated by 1.8 mu-s.
A white pulsed neutron beam was produced by
spallation of thick tungsten target by 800 MeV pulsed
proton beam.

x4freetext: Fission neutrons with energy bellow 1.59MeV
were detected using array of 22 Li-glass scintillation
detectors. 21 detectors used GS20 Li-glass enriched
with 95% of 6Li, one detector used GS30 Li-glass
enriched with 99.9% of 7Li. Five of these detectors
contained 1.27 cm thick Li-glass, the others were 1.80
cm thick. Each Li-glass was mounted to an R1250A
Hamamatsu photomultiplier tube. The nominal flight path
from the PPAC to a Li- glass detector
was (0.400+-0.005) m. Time resolution was (1.05+-1) ns.
Data presented in figs.19-22 of the reference
as ratio to MXW sent by author K.J.K. as spectrum
normalized to probability distribution. Results
obtained using Li glass (up to 1.5 MeV) and EJ-309
liquid scintillator (from 0.9 MeV to 10 MeV) overlap
in energy region 0.9 - 1.5 MeV. Covariance matrix
sent by author

x4freetext: Fission neutrons with energy above 0.89MeV
were detected with a 54-detector EJ-309 liquid
scintillator array, Each scintillator of cylindrical
shape with diameter of 17.7 cm and thickness of 5.5
cm  was coupled to an R4144 Hamamatsu PMT. Nominal
flight path was (1.020+-0.005) m from the PPAC.
Data presented in figs.19-22 of the reference
as ratio to MXW sent by author K.J.K. as spectrum
normalized to probability distribution.
